  <!-- SECTION 6: COREDNS -->
  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-label">// DIAGRAM 06</div>
    <h2>CoreDNS &amp; Service Discovery</h2>
    <p>CoreDNS is the default DNS server in Kubernetes. It resolves Service names to ClusterIPs and handles DNS queries from all Pods through the kube-dns ClusterIP (typically 10.96.0.10).</p>

    <div class="diagram-wrap">
      <div class="diagram-title">FIG 6.0 — DNS RESOLUTION FLOW IN KUBERNETES</div>

      <div class="dns-flow">
        <div class="dns-step">
          <div class="dns-num">1</div>
          <div class="dns-content">
            <span class="dns-query">Pod queries: my-service.my-namespace.svc.cluster.local</span>
            <span class="dns-result">→ Pod's /etc/resolv.conf points to 10.96.0.10 (kube-dns)</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="dns-step">
          <div class="dns-num">2</div>
          <div class="dns-content">
            <span class="dns-query">Request arrives at CoreDNS Pod (kube-system namespace)</span>
            <span class="dns-result">→ CoreDNS checks Kubernetes API for matching Service</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="dns-step">
          <div class="dns-num">3</div>
          <div class="dns-content">
            <span class="dns-query">CoreDNS returns A record: 10.96.45.123 (ClusterIP)</span>
            <span class="dns-result">→ For Headless Services, returns Pod IPs directly (no ClusterIP)</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="dns-step">
          <div class="dns-num">4</div>
          <div class="dns-content">
            <span class="dns-query">Pod connects to 10.96.45.123:80</span>
            <span class="dns-result">→ kube-proxy iptables rule load-balances to a backend Pod</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="dns-arch">
        <div class="dns-comp">
          <span class="dns-comp-name">CoreDNS</span>
          <span class="dns-comp-desc">Pluggable DNS server. Runs as Deployment in kube-system. Extensible via Corefile plugins.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="dns-comp">
          <span class="dns-comp-name" style="color:var(--accent3)">ndots:5</span>
          <span class="dns-comp-desc">Default search domain behaviour. Queries expand through 5 suffixes before going upstream.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="dns-comp">
          <span class="dns-comp-name" style="color:var(--accent4)">Headless Svc</span>
          <span class="dns-comp-desc">ClusterIP: None. Returns Pod IPs via DNS. Used for StatefulSets and direct Pod addressing.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

